<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: FILLMORE; QUARREL LEADS TO DRIVE-BY SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Fillmore man suffered serious bullet wounds and another was arrested in 
connection with a drive-by shooting that began with an earlier argument in 
Fillmore, sheriff's deputies said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Joel Lopez, 20, suffered several bullet wounds to the neck and abdomen while 
in front of his house in the 300 block of Del Valle Drive about 9:30 p.m. 
Thursday, Sheriff's Detective Raul Munoz said. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies, given descriptions of the gunman, arrested 18-year-old Reynaldo 
Villagomez about an hour later at his house in the 900 block of 3rd Street, not 
far from the site of the shooting, Munoz said. 
</P>
<P>
 He said Lopez, along with his brother and two men, had been standing in front 
of his house when a motorist in a dark-gray older Toyota pulled up. The two 
brothers approached the Toyota, words were exchanged, and the motorist fired a 
small-caliber handgun toward them. The bullets struck Lopez, detectives said. 
</P>
<P>
 After being driven to a relative's house on nearby Sespe Avenue, Lopez was 
taken to Santa Paula Memorial Hospital, where a nursing supervisor said he was 
in serious condition after undergoing surgery. 
</P>
<P>
 Villagomez was booked at the Ventura County Jail on suspicion of assault with 
a deadly weapon, Sgt. Jeff Matson said. Bail was $25,000 and Villagomez is to 
be arraigned Tuesday, Munoz said. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives had not determined whether the Thursday night shooting was 
gang-related, he said. GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
