<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOS ALAMITOS; MOVADOS WINS CALIFORNIA DERBY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STACY PIGOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Movados, fourth in the wagering, upset favored Jumping Tac Flash in the 
$80,000 California Derby on Friday night, winning his second start and his 
first major stakes race. 
</P>
<P>
 Movados is owned by Legacy Ranch and trained by Brian Koriner, the same team 
that took Daily Triple to victory in the Governor's Cup Derby in September. 
</P>
<P>
 Jockey Ralph Seville and Movados broke from post position eight in the 
10-horse derby field, easily covering the 400 yards in 19.92 seconds. The 
Charlie Bloomquist-trained Moo Vin First finished second, beaten a half-length. 
</P>
<P>
 The finish of the California Derby was highlighted by three deadheats. Jumping 
Tac Flash and Comes A Storm, the two fastest qualifiers to the derby, 
deadheated for the show position. The Money Crunch and Untamed Heart tied for 
fifth, while Sean Casady and Her First Cin deadheated for seventh. STACY PIGOTT 
</P>
