<P>
 IBM, Apple Close to Agreement on Common Hardware Standard: The two computer 
companies could be selling the machines within two years, an industry source 
said.The firms have been trying to work out a standard for computers using the 
PowerPC microprocessor that would allow them to run software for both Apple 
Inc.'s operating system and Microsoft Corp.'s industry-dominating Windows. An 
executive familiar with the talks said on condition of anonymity that IBM and 
Apple "are extremely close to defining a common platform" that would let the 
companies sell such computers in about two years. Developing the standard could 
persuade software developers to write more programs for both the Apple and IBM 
operating systems. 
