<HEADLINE>
<P>
DANCE REVIEW; DANZA TROUPE'S PROMISE UNFULFILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JENNIFER FISHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It all started so well. Brooding in amber light on a dark stage, Emilio 
Hernandez, the tall, dark and virtuosic force of Teatro de Danza Espanola, 
erupted in a fit of elegantly forceful moods, stopping and starting as if 
