<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: STUDIO CITY; WORKER DIES IN FALL FROM ROOF OF HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE TAMAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A construction worker apparently fell to his death Friday morning while 
repairing the chimney of a Studio City home, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 John Cisneros, 24, of Los Angeles had suffered what appeared to be severe neck 
injuries when he was discovered in the yard of a home in the 3700 block of 
Vantage Avenue, fire officials said.Police were investigating the death as an 
accident. 
</P>
<P>
 A neighbor spotted Cisneros' body about 9:30 a.m. and dialed paramedics, said 
Detective Mark Aragon of the Los Angeles Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Aragon said Cisneros was employed by an independent contractor and appeared to 
have been working alone when he fell. He had apparently been clearing debris 
from the roof of the house, which was having its chimney repaired. 
</P>
<P>
 An autopsy has tentatively been scheduled for today. 
</P>
<P>
 Rick Rice, a spokesman for Cal/OSHA, the state's industrial-safety agency, 
said his agency plans to investigate the death to determine how it occurred and 
whether state laws or regulations were violated. JULIE TAMAKI 
</P>
