<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; L.A. CIRCUS TO VISIT HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC SLATER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The big top will rise above Valley Presbyterian Hospital in Van Nuys today and 
the acrobats, elephants and clowns will come marching in. 
</P>
<P>
 The L.A. Circus has come to town and will offer three performances today, the 
first beginning at 11 a.m., and another three performances Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is the fourth annual circus sponsored by the hospital, and a way of 
"saying thanks to the community," said Valley Presbyterian spokeswoman Janna 
Wilson. 
</P>
<P>
 Presented by the L.A. Foundation of Circus Arts and the city's Cultural 
Affairs Department, the 90-minute shows will run at 11 a.m., 1 and 3 p.m. each 
day. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to the requisite old-fashioned circus performances, other events 
at the hospital -- 15107 Vanowen St. -- will include a circus clown workshop 
for children before each show, a classic car display and a bicycle safety 
course on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are $4 per person, $2 for those over 55, and children under 2 get in 
free. Tickets can be purchased at the gate before each show or in advance from 
the hospital's first-floor gift shop. ERIC SLATER 
</P>
