<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: TREEPEOPLE STAGING ANNUAL FUND-RAISER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ED BOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The environmental group TreePeople is holding its annual fund-raiser, "Evening 
Under the Harvest Moon," at its Coldwater Canyon Park headquarters tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 Featured in the $250-a-person fund-raiser will be a 10-minute film by David 
Zucker and Marshall Herskovitz about the work of the organization.Zucker was a 
producer of "Naked Gun," "Airplane" and other comedy movies, and Herskovitz was 
a creator of the television series "thirtysomething." 
</P>
<P>
 The film was still being edited as of Friday, said TreePeople spokesman Joel 
Brokaw, who added that it included some "lightness" to the material. It is 
meant to give a broader view of what TreePeople is all about. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's more than just planting trees," Brokaw said, adding that they wanted to 
get across the message that people can do a lot to help in their own 
neighborhood. "What TreePeople is about is getting young people and adults 
involved in making that personal difference." 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets may be purchased at the door or by calling (310) 393-5600. Parking is 
available at Harvard-Westlake High School with shuttle service to the event. ED 
BOND 
</P>
