<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: SAN PEDRO; MECHANICAL 
BREAKDOWN BLAMED IN TRUCK CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police said Friday that a mechanical problem apparently caused a runaway truck 
to crash through a San Pedro home, leaving an elderly woman seriously injured 
when the vehicle pinned her against a stove. 
</P>
<P>
 Dora Myron, 70, of Rancho Palos Verdes was in guarded condition at Harbor-UCLA 
Medical Center in Torrance.She suffered a broken right leg, broken left ankle 
and chest injuries in Thursday's accident. 
</P>
<P>
 Police Officer Gary Robinson said no charges had been filed against the driver 
of the truck, Raul Garcia Munoz, 20. 
</P>
<P>
 The five-ton flatbed truck carrying trash dumpsters was parked atop a hill 
when it began rolling about 2:30 p.m. Thursday, said Fire Department spokesman 
Brian Humphrey. 
</P>
<P>
 The truck rolled down a narrow residential street, jumped a curb, struck a 
light pole and knocked down a tree, carrying part of the trunk inside the 
wood-frame house. 
</P>
</TEXT>
