<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTIVE IN SLAYING REMAINS UNCLEAR; SHOOTING: VICTIM BENITA MIKAILIAN, 40, IS 
DESCRIBED AS A SUCCESSFUL, HARD-WORKING TRAVEL AGENT. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE RYFLE and GEOFFREY MOHAN, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Friends and business acquaintances remained shocked and mystified Friday at 
the fatal shooting of a 40-year-old travel agent, whose body was found in her 
North Brand Boulevard office Thursday morning. 
</P>
<P>
 Those who knew the victim, Benita Mikailian, said she frequently kept late 
hours at her agency, Benita's Travel Town, at 1110 N. Brand Boulevard.The 
business thrived, and Mikailian entertained a circle of well-heeled friends at 
her exclusive Park Towers condominium on Pioneer Drive, just blocks from her 
office. 
</P>
<P>
 "She was a serious businesswoman," said Joe Ayvazi, an agent with the Fred 
Sands Broadway Realtors office located downstairs from the travel agency. "It 
seemed like she had a really successful operation." 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale Police Department investigators were mum Friday on details of the 
homicide, but a resident at her building said they visited Mikailian's 
condominium and took photographs. She had lived in a first-floor unit of the 
18-story building for about four years, according to real estate records. 
</P>
<P>
 Acquaintances said she lived alone in the two-bedroom unit and could not 
recall mention of any relatives. 
</P>
<P>
 Mikailian's body was discovered in her second-floor office by an employee 
reporting to work at 8:30 a.m. Thursday, according to police. They would not 
comment on a motive for the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 "From what I heard, apparently nothing was stolen," said Ayvazi. "She had a 
gold Rolex watch on, and jewelry, but nothing was touched." 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said Mikailian probably was killed after 8 p.m. Wednesday. 
Employees at the real estate agency said she often worked until 9 or 10 p.m., 
but would lock the door of her office after 5 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
