<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; TRUCK HIJACKED BY 2 PITCHESS ESCAPEES FOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE TAMAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A truck hijacked by two inmates who escaped from the Peter J. Pitchess Honor 
Rancho was found a few blocks from the East Los Angeles home of one of the 
prisoners Friday, but the two escapees remained at large, Los Angeles police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jesus Guerrero, 23, and Mario Garate, 19, escaped Tuesday night and later 
stole a truck from two college students parked outside a hotel near the Magic 
Mountain theme park. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles police found the abandoned truck Friday morning in the 1700 block 
of Workman Street in Lincoln Heights, just a few blocks away from Garate's 
home, Officer Susan Padron of the Los Angeles Police Department said. She said 
it had been stripped of its battery, tires and other parts. 
</P>
<P>
 "I have a strong belief that he's within the area," Padron said of Garate. 
</P>
<P>
 Garate, who was serving time for spousal abuse, and Guerrero, who was jailed 
on a narcotics charge, escaped from a processing center in a minimum security 
area where about 200 other inmates were gathered, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The pair managed to pass a razor wire fence between the processing center and 
the outside wall of the jail. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said both men had been scheduled to be transferred to a 
higher-security facility because they had caused trouble among other inmates. 
JULIE TAMAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
