<HEADLINE>
<P>
SWAT TEAM EXHIBITION TO HIGHLIGHT SAFETY DAY EVENTS IN NEWPORT BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Most people never get any closer to a police Special Weapons and Tactics team 
than what they see on their television sets, but residents will have a chance 
to see the city's SWAT team in action Sunday as part of a Safety Day 
demonstration. 
</P>
<P>
 The SWAT team exercise is one highlight of the event, which will also include 
displays of fire and rescue equipment and services, lifeguard and Sheriff's 
Harbor Patrol operations, and building department safety tips. 
</P>
<P>
 With the Laguna Beach fire a recent memory, building department officials hope 
that homeowners will turn out for a roofing fair to learn about ways to protect 
their homes with fire-resistant roofs. 
</P>
<P>
 Representatives of roofing manufacturers and contractors will demonstrate 
roofing installations, while firefighters will supervise a demonstration of a 
roof fire and sprinkler system. 
</P>
<P>
 Building Department officials will provide information on earthquake-safe 
construction.  
</P>
<P>
 Displays throughout the 10 a.m. to 3 p.m. event will include the Newport Beach 
police helicopter, its K-9 team, fire and rescue equipment, and lifesaving 
techniques by the American Red Cross.  
</P>
<P>
 The SWAT demonstration and a firefighting demonstration will both take place 
at noon. 
</P>
<P>
 Parking for the event is free.  
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the Building Department at 644-3275 or the Fire 
Department at 644-3106.HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
