<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHEELCHAIR TENNIS TOURNAMENT OPENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More than 350 wheelchair tennis players from 25 countries will compete in the 
15th U.S. Open Wheelchair Tennis Championships today through Oct. 16 at the 
Racquet Club of Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is the culmination of the Grand Prix circuit, which includes 70 
wheelchair tennis events nationwide. The event begins with competition in the 
junior, masters and mixed doubles divisions. 
</P>
<P>
 Competition is scheduled in various skill divisions each day beginning at 9 
a.m. The women's open singles finals will be at noon Oct. 15, the men's open 
singles finals at noon Oct. 16. 
</P>
<P>
 The tournament is organized by the San Clemente-based National Foundation of 
Wheelchair Tennis. 
</P>
