<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; STRONG SECOND HALF SPARKS MATER DEI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mater Dei football Coach Bruce Rollinson didn't want his team getting in a 
scoring contest with Riverside Ramona Friday night, so the Monarchs made it a 
one-sided show in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 The Monarchs, the second-ranked team in Orange County, pulled away in the 
second half to beat Ramona, 30-14, in a nonleague football game. 
</P>
<P>
 The score was tied, 14-14, midway through the third quarter, but Mater Dei put 
the game away with touchdown runs of four and one yards by Steve Bodnar and Pat 
Shinnefield's 47-yard field goal. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was afraid of getting in a scoring contest and that's what ended up 
happening," Rollinson said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Monarchs marched 80 yards in 10 plays on their opening drive and took a 
7-0 lead on a 14-yard run by Bodnar. 
</P>
<P>
 Bodnar finished with 178 yards in 16 carries and scored four touchdowns. Joe 
Trampush added 102 yards in 13 carries for Mater Dei (5-0). 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams (4-1) tied it later in the first quarter when Nian Taylor broke loose 
on a 92-yard punt return. But on the next play from scrimmage, Bodnar had an 
80-yard touchdown run to give Mater Dei a 14-7 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Ramona moved deep into Mater Dei territory twice in the second quarter, but 
missed a 39-field goal attempt and later was stopped on a fourth and one at the 
Mater Dei 15. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams tied it, 14-14, in the third quarter when J.B. LaCombe caught a pass 
three yards past the line of scrimmage and lateraled it to Taylor, who went 55 
yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
