<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; BROWN, TAFT HAVE IT THEIR WAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PETER YOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jerry Brown had a field day. And as Brown went, so too, did Taft High in a 
53-0 rout of Chatsworth on the Chancellors' home field Friday night in a 
Northwest Valley Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown, a senior, rushed for a career-high 226 yards and four touchdowns in 14 
carries, and Taft (4-1 overall, 2-0 in league play) scored on each of its 
possessions. 
</P>
<P>
 "Everything was going good tonight," Brown understated. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown scored the game's first three touchdowns on runs of 35, 19 and six 
yards. He had 134 yards in the first half as Taft forged a 25-0 lead. And if 
that wasn't enough, on his first carry of the second half, he burst through the 
middle and raced untouched for an 80-yard touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Chatsworth (2-3, 0-2) gained only 92 yards and had a 63-yard touchdown pass 
negated because of a holding penalty. 
</P>
<P>
 Taft gained 438 yards, including 377 on the ground. Quarterback Dayon Shaw 
completed five of nine passes for 61 yards and two touchdowns. Dashon Polk 
scored on an 88-yard run up the middle and a five-yard pass. Friday's Yardstick 
</P>
