<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPRADLIN CONVERTS FOR LITTLEROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RON STAPP, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robbie Spradlin kicked a 26-yard field goal with eight seconds left to lift 
Littlerock High to a 9-7 nonleague victory over Saugus on Friday night at 
Canyon High. 
</P>
<P>
 It was Spradlin's first field-goal attempt.Earlier, he missed a crucial extra 
point. "I was scared," he said, crying in the middle of a wild celebration. 
"But you have to make it." 
</P>
<P>
 Saugus took a 7-6 lead with 10 minutes left on Russell Overstreet's one-yard 
run. Derek Lyons added the extra point for Saugus (2-2-1). However, with two 
minutes left, Littlerock (2-1-2) drove from its 48-yard line to the Saugus 
nine, setting up Spradlin's second-down kick. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lobos intercepted three passes by Saugus quarterback Kevin Carrasco, who 
completed four of 21 for 67 yards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Prep Sports; Game Story 
</P>
