<P>
BISHOP DIEGO GETS PAST NORDHOFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES CHESNUTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Josh Hawkins of Nordhoff High rushed for 148 yards and scored three 
touchdowns, but Bishop Diego defeated the Rangers, 33-32, in a nonleague game 
Friday night at Nordhoff. 
</P>
<P>
 The game included seven lead changes and was up for grabs until the final 
minute. 
</P>
<P>
 Gabriel Sanchez of Bishop Diego (2-3) scored the winning touchdown on a 
26-yard run with 2:58 left. He also scored on a 95-yard kickoff return to open 
the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Hawkins scored on runs of two and 60 yards and a 40-yard pass play for 
Nordhoff (3-2). Ranger quarterback Mike Gardia completed nine of 10 passes in 
the first half, but only three of 11 in the second. JAMES CHESNUTT 
