<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; BERG HELPS LA HABRA HAND LA SERNA ITS 
FIRST LOSS OF SEASON, 31-7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON HILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Will McIntosh caught three of Sonje Berg's four touchdown passes as La Habra 
pounded previously unbeaten Whittier La Serna, 31-7, Friday night at California 
High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Berg was 12 of 18 for 253 yards and McIntosh caught six of passes for 183 
yards. 
</P>
<P>
 A fumble recovery by Juan Garcia set up La Habra's first score. On a swing 
pass, Berg found receiver Keven Ness, who ran 37 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra (2-3) scored again when McIntosh caught a 59-yard pass from Berg to 
give the Highlanders a 13-0 lead with 9:46 left in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 An interception by La Serna's Daniel Bruen with 29 seconds left in the first 
half proved costly for the Highlanders. The Lancers, whose offense had 
accumulated only 97 total yards, scored when Matt Friscoe took a pitch from 
Mike Hale and connected with George on a 55-yard scoring pass. 
</P>
<P>
 After a combined five penalties and four turnovers by both teams to open the 
third quarter, the Highlanders finally opened up the game when Berg found 
McIntosh with a 41-yard touchdown pass. La Habra later increased its lead to 
24-7 after a 24-yard field goal by Chris Diaz. 
</P>
<P>
 Aaron Kosarefss recovered a fumble on the ensuing kickoff to give the 
Highlanders the ball at La Serna's 18-yard line. Berg found McIntosh in the end 
zone on the next play to extend La Habra's lead to 31-7. JASON HILL 
</P>
</TEXT>
