<HEADLINE>
<P>
BENNETT PACES SIMI VALLEY, 24-20 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LANCE O'FALLON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Quarterback Tim Bennett threw for two touchdowns and ran for another to lead 
Simi Valley to a 24-20 victory over Thousand Oaks Friday night in a Marmonte 
League game at Simi Valley High. 
</P>
<P>
 Bennett completed 18 of 24 passes for 228 yards for Simi Valley (4-0-1, 2-0 in 
league play). 
</P>
<P>
 Bennett directed the game-winning, 80-yard drive in six plays. He connected 
with Chris Miller on a 33-yard pass play with 7 minutes 58 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks (1-4, 0-2) took a 20-17 lead early in the fourth quarter when 
Frank Coletta scored on a three-yard run. LANCE O'FALLON 
</P>
