<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; INTERCEPTION SETS UP CANYON'S VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DALE RUHE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Clay Kilbarger kicked a 46-yard field goal as time expired to give Canyon High 
a 6-3 victory over Corona in a nonleague football game Friday at Corona High 
School. 
</P>
<P>
 The winning field goal was set up on the third interception of the game by 
Canyon defensive back Greg Jacobs, who returned an errant pass by Corona 
quarterback Mike Knox 58 yards to the Panther 31-yard line with five seconds 
remaining in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 "Knox likes to look at just one receiver on each play," Jacobs said. "Once I 
saw him locked into the receiver, I went for the ball and got it." 
</P>
<P>
 Jacobs intercepted his first pass with 8 minutes 9 seconds remaining in the 
fourth quarter, but the Comanches were stopped after three plays and forced to 
punt. When Corona regained possession, a Knox pass was deflected by Troy Mills 
into Jacobs' hands. Jacobs returned it 39 yards to midfield, but once again 
Canyon was stopped after three plays and forced to punt. 
</P>
<P>
 Corona kicker Andy Omlor kicked a 27-yard field goal with 6:16 remaining in 
the first quarter. Kilbarger countered with a 39-yard field goal with 54 
seconds left in the quarter to tie the score. 
</P>
<P>
 Corona outgained Canyon in total offense, 209-170. The Panther defense held 
Canyon quarterback Adam Hoover to eight completions in 23 attempts for 74 
yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Comanches' leading rusher was Cody Miller with 55 yards in 13 carries. 
DALE RUHE 
</P>
</TEXT>
