<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; BUENA PARK DEFENSE DELIVERS 20-7 
VICTORY OVER BELLFLOWER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL LYNCH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Buena Park linebacker Hung Thai returned an interception 100 yards and Jude 
Reyes kicked two field goals as Buena Park won its first game of the season by 
defeating Bellflower, 20-7, Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Bellflower quarterback Jonathon Rivers appeared to be driving his team for the 
game's first score after the Buccaneers recovered a Buena Park fumble on the 
Coyote 35 yard line.But a third-and-goal pass from the four was intercepted by 
Thai at the goal line. He raced down the left sideline to give the Coyotes a 
7-0 lead in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Bellflower was trailing, 10-0, in the third quarter when running back Sean 
Rumboiz capped a nine-play, 74-yard drive with a four-yard touchdown run. 
</P>
<P>
 But Buena Park answered with a 92-yard touchdown drive, capped by running back 
Aaron Hudson's 12-yard touchdown run. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena Park put the game away midway through the fourth quarter, when Reyes 
kicked a 40-yard field goal. 
</P>
<P>
 While the Buena Park offense controlled the game, Coyote linebackers Niel 
Flores, Robert Leventhal and Osualdo Olmos kept Bellflower off-balance with 
blitzes. MICHAEL LYNCH 
</P>
</TEXT>
