<HEADLINE>
<P>
VERDUGO HILLS SHUT OUT AGAIN, 42-0; FOOTBALL: WILSON BLANKS THE DONS, WHO HAVE 
NOT SCORED IN NINE QUARTERS. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE DESMOND, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Haunted by the fact that it had scored in only two of its last 12 quarters, 
Verdugo Hills High additionally faced the specter of Arlin Slayton on Friday 
afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 Wilson High's junior tailback rushed for 244 yards in 17 carries and scored 
three touchdowns to lead the Mules to a 42-0 romp over the Dons in a Northern 
Conference game at Verdugo Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Of Slayton's 17 carries, 12 netted 11 yards or more. Slayton scored on runs of 
16, 18 and 47 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dons, (0-3-2 overall, 0-1-1 in conference play), who last week tied 
Belmont, 0-0, have gone nine quarters without scoring. Their best chance came 
in the third quarter Friday, when quarterback David Kelly (80 yards in 10 
carries) appeared to score on an 80-yard run. However, the play was called back 
because of a clipping penalty. 
</P>
<P>
 Kelly had three passes intercepted, two by Buster Bradley, who returned the 
second 69 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 A safety and Slayton's first touchdown gave Wilson (4-1, 2-0) a 9-0 lead at 
halftime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
