<P>
By BEN STURTEVANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After blowing a 27-point lead, Coronado defeated Laguna Beach, 39-34, when 
Ledge Hakes scored with no time remaining Friday at Coronado High. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach (1-4) took a 34-33 lead when Liam McDonagh scored on a four-yard 
run with 1 minute 22 seconds left in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Hakes' touchdown followed a blocked 25-yard field-goal attempt by Coronado 
with 17 seconds left. Laguna Beach Coach Mike Roche argued that the field-goal 
attempt should have been Coronado's last play. 
</P>
<P>
 "That clock should have been running," he said. "I thought we'd won the game. 
But I'm not going to blame the officials. We came out flat and didn't play for 
three quarters. I just didn't have them ready." 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach was outclassed early. The Artists trailed 20 at the half and 27-0 
midway through the the third quarter after Hakes blew up the right sideline for 
a 63-yard touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach quarterback Nate Pivaroff put the Artists on the board with 
42-yard touchdown run. Sean Dixon answered on the Coronado's first play from 
scrimmage following the kickoff with a 71-yard touchdown run. Dixon's touchdown 
gave Coronado a 33-6 lead. From that point Laguna Beach scored four consecutive 
touchdowns. BEN STURTEVANT 
</P>
