<TEXT>
<P>
 Brendan McGraw rushed for 254 yards in 26 carries and scored four touchdowns, 
including a 32-yard touchdown catch, to lead Laguna Hills to a 38-3 victory 
over Dana Hills Friday night at Dana Hills High School.  
</P>
<P>
 McGraw, who is tied for the county lead with Los Amigos' Greg Fausto with 18 
touchdowns, scored on runs of 78, 40 and one yard before leaving the game after 
the third quarter.Not bad for a guy who was running behind a patchwork 
offensive line. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're a bit banged up and we have three guys on the offensive line who have 
been hurt and would have been playing tonight," said Laguna Hills Coach Steve 
Bresnahan. 
</P>
<P>
 "But Brendan McGraw is a good running back and we feel that if we can just 
hold the blocks for a second that every time he touches the ball, something 
good is going to happen," Bresnahan said. 
</P>
<P>
 On Laguna Hills' second play from scrimmage, McGraw ran off tackle 78 yards 
untouched for the Hawks' first score. 
</P>
<P>
 On the third play of the next possession, McGraw ran 40 yards for the Hawks' 
second touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills finished its scoring in the third quarter when, after Sako 
Yakinian kicked a 26-yard field goal, Brian Genuser threw 52 yards to Andy 
Roman for the game's final score. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills was also tough on defense, holding Dana Hills to 104 yards in the 
game, 44 in the second half. JOE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
