<P>
ROUNDUP; MASTER'S EXTENDS SOCCER STREAK TO 7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lucas Principe and Daryl Topalian each scored two goals as The Master's soccer 
team extended its undefeated streak to seven matches with a 7-0 nonconference 
victory over host Menlo College on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Master's (11-1-1), the No. 12-ranked team in the NAIA Division I poll, has not 
lost a match since a 3-0 defeat to Westmont three weeks ago. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was pleased to play everybody and rest a couple of injured players," 
Master's Coach Jim Rickard said. 
</P>
<P>
 "This trip gave me a good idea about the depth of our team." 
</P>
<P>
 Four starters did not play because of injuries.  
</P>
<P>
 Backup goalie Mark Anderson had three saves for the Mustangs and posted his 
second shutout of the season. MEN'S CROSS-COUNTRY 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine Invitational -- Riverside College, led by individual winner Wilhelm 
Gidabuday, swept the first four places, but Glendale's superior depth propelled 
the Vaqueros to victory in the meet at Irvine Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale, led by Jacques Salsberg's sixth-place finish, placed five runners 
among the first 12 finishers for a 45-point total.  
</P>
<P>
 Riverside, third in last year's state championships, was second with 52 
points, followed by El Camino (86), San Diego Mesa (128) and Rancho Santiago 
(169). 
</P>
<P>
 Salsberg timed 20 minutes 14 seconds over the four-mile course.  
</P>
<P>
 He was followed by teammates Eduardo Macias (eighth in 20:40), Nacho Delgado 
(ninth in 20:42), Jose Padilla (10th in 20:44) and Jose Arias (12th in 20:48). 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside's fifth -- and final -- scoring runner finished 45th. WOMEN'S 
CROSS-COUNTRY 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine Invitational -- Tanya Janet of Glendale placed 12th to lead the 
Vaqueros to an 11th-place finish in the meet at Irvine Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Janet timed 21:01 over the 5,000-meter course as Glendale totaled 281 points. 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego Mesa placed first with 72 points, followed by El Camino (73) and 
defending state champion Irvine Valley (103). MEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego State 1, Cal State Northridge 0 -- Dan Tomlin scored an unassisted 
goal in the 63rd minute to lead the Aztecs in a Mountain Pacific Sports 
Federation Pacific Division opener for both teams at North Campus Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Keith Rosenberg had six of Northridge's nine shots on goal as the Matadors 
(6-4 overall) lost for the third consecutive time at home and the second time 
this season to the Aztecs (7-4). WOMEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 7, Santa Monica 0 -- Tara Gilroy scored two goals to lead the Raiders 
(4-2 overall, 2-0 in Western State Conference play) in a match at Santa Monica. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark's Caprice Conley was red-carded in the 50th minute when she was 
involved in an altercation with Santa Monica's goalkeeper.  
</P>
<P>
 Both must sit out their next match. WOMEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran d. Whittier, 15-2, 15-6, 15-6 -- Darcy White had 11 kills to lead 
the Regals to victory in the Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic 
Conference match. 
</P>
<P>
 Liz Martinez added 31 assists and nine digs for Cal Lutheran (12-6, 4-0). 
GIRLS' TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
 La Reina 11, Righetti 7 -- The doubles teams of Vicki Hull-Katie Nelson and 
Catherine Chien-Heather Szabo each swept three matches to lead host La Reina 
(6-2) in a nonleague match. 
</P>
