<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; MARINA TOPS OCEAN VIEW, MOVES TO 5-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC MADDY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marina improved to 5-0, its best start since 1981, with a 34-7 nonleague 
victory over Ocean View on Friday at Westminster High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vikings consistently started with good field position, with six of their 
10 possessions starting in Ocean View territory thanks to good special teams 
play and two Seahawk turnovers. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vikings' Mike Williams rushed for a game-high 114 yards and a touchdown in 
the first half, but sat out the second half icing a twisted right ankle. 
Williams, who has rushed for 668 yards this season, is expected to play in 
Thursday's Sunset League opener at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
 Marina took a 7-0 lead midway through the opening quarter, as Chad Scuncio 
intercepted a Ted Norman pass at the Seahawk 6 and Williams scored three plays 
later on a one-yard run. The Vikings increased the lead to 17-0 at the half on 
a six-yard scoring pass from Matt Roberson to Joe Borzoni and a 40-yard field 
goal by Peter Mignosa. 
</P>
<P>
 Borzoni ran the second-half kickoff back 62 yards to the Ocean View 31. Micah 
Harrison eventually scored on a four-yard run to make it 24-0.  
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View got on the board with 5:05 left in the game, as Jason Hoffman 
scored on a one-yard run. The Seahawks have lost 34 consecutive games, the 
longest current losing streak in the state. ERIC MADDY 
</P>
</TEXT>
