PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; CORONA DEL MAR STORMS PAST SANTA ANA 
VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT FARMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The battle between two of Orange County's finest running backs never 
materialized as Corona del Mar scored early and often to beat Santa Ana Valley, 
55-13, Friday night at Newport Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
 Sea King senior Brian Hogan gained 159 yards in 23 carries and teammate Josh 
Walz rushed for 123 yards in 10 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana Valley senior Dwayne Cherrington was limited to 48 yards in 16 
carries as the Sea King defense kept the Falcons (2-3) to 130 yards in total 
offense. 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar (2-3) connected on its first drive, as Darren MacDonald caught 
a 14 yard screen pass from Walz just 5 minutes 38 seconds into the game. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sea Kings led 13-0 after one quarter after J.J. DiCesare ran five yards 
for the first of his two rushing touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 DiCesare finished the game with 68 yards in six carries. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sea King defense kept the Falcons off guard all evening. Billy Taketa ran 
an interception 46 yards for a touchdown in the second quarter and Fred Garcia 
recovered two fumbles, the latter for a Corona del Mar touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 After Walz's four-yard touchdown run early in the third quarter, the Falcons' 
Kyle Marks took the ensuing kickoff 93 yards for a touchdown. MATT FARMER 
</P>
