PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; HOLLOWAY SCORES 3 TOUCHDOWNS FOR ORANGE 
LUTHERAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANDY EISER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Che Holloway scored three touchdowns and Matt Stratton booted a school-record 
48-yard field goal as Orange Lutheran rolled to a 41-0 nonleague victory over 
Pasadena Marshall Friday night at Brea-Olinda High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Holloway, recovering from lower back spasms suffered two weeks ago, rushed for 
a five-yard score on his first carry and added touchdown runs of two and 49 
yards in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Stratton made his record kick midway through the third quarter after the 
Lancers (4-1) got possession following Jake Anderson's safety. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Joe Juliano led a balanced Orange Lutheran attack, passing for 178 
yards and a touchdown, and running for 94 yards and a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Marshall quarterback Jonathan Chambers completed only eight of 23 passes for 
71 yards and had three passes intercepted as the Eagles fell to 0-5. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran's Aaron Kenney led all receivers with three receptions for 74 
yards, while Dan Young added an 18-yard touchdown reception. 
</P>
<P>
 Patrick Walker was the Eagles' only real threat, accounting for 76 yards total 
offense, on five rushes and five receptions. ANDY EISER 
</P>
