<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; SANTIAGO'S SOKANTHONG TOWERS OVER BOLSA 
GRANDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICK CHRISTOPHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There was nothing small about the numbers Santiago running back Tom 
Sokanthong, all 5 feet 7 inches of him, put up against visiting Bolsa Grande on 
Friday night at Garden Grove High. 
</P>
<P>
 The senior rushed for 118 yards and two touchdowns to lead the Cavaliers to a 
33-12 victory over Bolsa Grande in Garden Grove League action.Sokanthong added 
another 38 yards in offense on kickoff returns. 
</P>
<P>
 Santiago's rushing attack of 268 yards was spread among five rushers and wide 
receiver Octavio Villa scored twice. 
</P>
<P>
 Santiago took advantage Steve Lopez's 16-yard interception return to Bolsa 
Grande's 23 to set up the first of Sokanthong's five scores. He took a pitch 
from Christian Cortezand ran 14 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Only minutes later Cortez found Villa for a 69-yard scoring bomb. Cortez added 
another score himself running one in from 10 yards out in the third quarter for 
a 27-6 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Bolsa Grande (1-4, 0-2) scored early in the first minute of the second quarter 
on Eric Shaner's 12-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 Villa scored his second touchdown on a 10-yard run with 9:31 remaining in the 
half to give the Cavaliers a 21-6 lead. RICK CHRISTOPHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
