<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; CLEARY'S FIELD GOALS GIVE GARDEN GROVE 
25-12 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sophomore Ryan Cleary connected on three field goals, the longest from 49 
yards, to help propel Garden Grove to a 25-12 victory over Pacifica in a Garden 
Grove League game Friday night at Bolsa Grande Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Cleary hit on tries of 38, 44 and 49 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 "We felt that it was as good as a punt," Coach Ralph Stevens said. 
</P>
<P>
 Cleary gave Garden Grove (3-2, 2-0 in league) a 3-0 lead with his 38-yard 
field goal and Garden Grove increased its advantage to 5-0 when Darrel Paplia 
tackled Mike Fernandez in the end zone for a safety. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica (1-4, 0-2) took its only lead of the game when Tommy Summers scored 
from 11 yards, but the two-point conversion effort failed. 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove quickly regained the advantage on the next play from scrimmage, 
when Troy Haller hit Gerardo Lopez with a 67-yard touchdown pass and Cleary's 
conversion made the lead 12-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Cleary hit a 44-yard field goal with 22 seconds left in the first half to 
increase the Garden Grove lead to 15-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica put together a 63-yard scoring drive capped by a three-yard scoring 
run by Summers on the opening drive of the second half to cut the lead to 
15-12. 
</P>
<P>
 The Argonauts regained a six-point lead on Cleary's 49-yard field goal with 48 
seconds left in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica's final opportunity to tie and possibly take the lead was stopped 
midway in the final quarter when a fourth-down pass was dropped and Garden 
Grove put the game out of reach on Ruben Reyna's 18-yard touchdown run with 
2:18 left. MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
