<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP EXTRA / SATURDAY FOOTBALL PULLOUT; FAUSTO SCORES FIVE TOUCHDOWNS IN LOS 
AMIGOS' 42-13 ROUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL CASEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Greg Fausto scored five touchdowns Friday night to lead Los Amigos to a 42-13 
victory over host Aliso Niguel. Fausto scored on runs of four, four, three, 
five and nine yards, and shares the county lead in touchdowns with 18. 
</P>
<P>
 The 5-foot-8, 140-pound junior gained 157 yards in 25 carries. He has 658 
yards rushing this season. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lobos (5-0), ranked fifth in Orange County, overwhelmed the first-year 
Wolverines (2-3) in total offense, 414-135. 
</P>
<P>
 Fausto's two touchdowns in the opening quarter gave Los Amigos an early, 13-0 
lead. But Aliso Niguel made a game of it in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 First, defensive end Ryan Wiedeman returned an interception for a five-yard 
touchdown. Trailing, 20-7, Aliso Niguel pulled off a successful hook-and-ladder 
play. Quarterback Scott Nemeth threw to Justin Martin, who lateraled to Andrew 
Mashburn. 
</P>
<P>
 Mashburn ran the final 60 yards of the 68-yard play, cutting the Lobos' lead 
to seven at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 But Los Amigos wore down Aliso Niguel in the second half, limiting them to 
just 14 yards on 12 plays and no first downs. And the Wolverines were hurt by 
five turnovers in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Lobos quarterback Ape Tuato was 10 of 15 for 174 yards including a 
fourth-down, 21-yard touchdown pass to Warren Roberge. Nemeth completed 10 of 
19 for 96 yards. MICHAEL CASEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
