<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGELS NAME BLYLEVEN MINOR LEAGUE COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bert Blyleven rejoined the Angel organization Friday when he was named 
pitching coach of Class-A Cedar Rapids. 
</P>
<P>
 Blyleven, who pitched four years for the Angels, rejoins the organization 
after being a roving instructor during the 1993 season. This summer, he told 
Angel General Manager Bill Bavasi he wanted to coach, and that he wants to be a 
pitching coach in the majors. 
</P>
<P>
 The Angels also released pitcher John Dopson (1-4, 6.14 earned-run average), 
who had not pitched since June 22 because of an inflamed right shoulder. The 
Angels have 38 players on their 40-man roster. 
</P>
</TEXT>
